Who this joanna was ie unknown. The little poem is a gem even among Johnston's. On Wedderbum see No. XXIX. os Vol. 1.

1. Jorrusrou,

assumunt.

Sudden death harh linked the tomb to the bridal conch, the funereal torch to the marriage flambeau. A maiden she was when winter begam a spouse when at its height, and soon, when it had passed away, she was only ashes cold. Fortune's wheel is fickle, pleasure is ever fleeting, man's hope is alway slippery and his life a span.
